  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Chop the <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into bite-sized pieces</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped potato</strong> to a heatproof bowl, then cover the bowl with <strong>cling film </strong>and pierce a few holes in the top with a fork</p><p>Put the bowl in the <strong>microwave</strong> for 4-5 min <span class=\"text-danger\">[6-8 min]</span> or until the potatoes are fork-tender</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1679660028325-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1679660028325-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1679660028325-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1679660028325-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1679660028325-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the potatoes are cooking, add the<strong> panko breadcrumbs</strong> to a plate with a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and season with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper </strong>and give everything a good mix up</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1679660035302-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
